claims:
1. the preparation method of a starch-base biodegradation material is characterized in that feed composition is by weight:
      Starch 70-85,
      Amylase 0.05-0.5,
      Acetylating agent 1-11,
      Softening agent 4-14,
      Hydrophobically modified agent 3-6,
      Biomass polymkeric substance 5-20;
      Preparation process is as follows:
      1) add water and add amylase in starch, put into the high-speed mixing stirrer, be warming up to 60-120 ℃, stir gelatinization in 5-10 minute, wherein, starch is starch with the ratio that cooperates of water by weight: water=1: 0.3～1;
      2) in the step 1) product, add acetylating agent, under the stirring velocity of 100-900rpm stirring reaction 5-30 minute;
      3) in step 2) add softening agent in the product, continue to stir 5-30 minute;
      4) in the step 3) product, add the hydrophobically modified agent, continued churning time 5-30 minute, obtain starch gel;
      5) add the biomass polymkeric substance in the step 4) gained starch gel, mix and stirred 5-20 minute, mix the back blowing, send into extruding pelletization on the parallel dual-screw extruding machine, obtain starch-base biodegradation material.Wherein, the screw slenderness ratio of parallel dual-screw extruding machine is 48: 1, screw speed 100-300rpm, and each is distinguished temperature and is controlled at: a district 60-100 ℃; Two district 130-150 ℃; Three district 140-170 ℃; Four district 140-180 ℃; Five district 120-150 ℃.
